This paper is about using deep neural networks for dialogue applications, specifically generative sequence-to-sequence models. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Sound). These sub-categories are likely because the paper discusses the use of neural networks for dialogue generation, which is a common topic in these areas of computer science.
